<i>I need to stand on my own...</i>

249
00:16:04,255 --> 00:16:05,715
What?

250
00:16:11,596 --> 00:16:13,097
[Sawa] <i>Kasuga...</i>

251
00:16:14,223 --> 00:16:15,391
Bye-bye.

252
00:16:21,981 --> 00:16:23,399
[Takao] Nakamura!

253
00:16:26,986 --> 00:16:28,070
Sorry...

254
00:16:28,654 --> 00:16:30,156
I thought you were someone else.

255
00:16:40,374 --> 00:16:42,126
-[chuckles softly]
-[indistinct chatter]

256
00:16:42,210 --> 00:16:44,337
<i>As if I could ever forget her...</i>

257
00:16:46,005 --> 00:16:47,715
<i>Where are you?</i>

258
00:16:48,758 --> 00:16:50,259
<i>What are you doing?</i>

259
00:16:51,135 --> 00:16:52,970
<i>Nakamura...</i>

260
00:16:53,054 --> 00:16:55,097
[laughing]

261
00:17:00,519 --> 00:17:02,438
-[splatters]
-Oh.

262
00:17:04,857 --> 00:17:05,983
[groaning]

263
00:17:06,067 --> 00:17:09,320
Hey! How dare you knock over
Mr. Tetsu's bowl of <i>oden.</i>

264
00:17:10,196 --> 00:17:13,532
I'm sorry. Let me pay for it... please.

265
00:17:13,616 --> 00:17:14,742
Pay for it?

266
00:17:14,825 --> 00:17:16,661
You think that's gonna be enough?

267
00:17:16,744 --> 00:17:19,789
Do you know what
Mr. Tetsu's <i>shirataki</i> noodles are worth?

268
00:17:19,872 --> 00:17:21,999
-His <i>shirataki </i>noodles!
-[Tetsu] Calm down, now.

269
00:17:22,500 --> 00:17:25,586
[chuckles] I'm not a monster.

270
00:17:26,128 --> 00:17:28,839
Why don't we go have a chat over there?

271
00:17:34,971 --> 00:17:36,722
All right, then.

272
00:17:37,390 --> 00:17:40,268
Give me all the money you got.

273
00:17:40,351 --> 00:17:41,352
[Takao] What?

274
00:17:41,978 --> 00:17:43,771
But...

275
00:17:43,854 --> 00:17:46,607
I'm really disappointed
that I couldn't eat my <i>shirataki.</i>

276
00:17:47,108 --> 00:17:49,193
That was the last one in the store.

277
00:17:49,277 --> 00:17:50,778
It's the least you can do.

278
00:17:52,113 --> 00:17:53,281
[Takao] No...

279
00:17:56,784 --> 00:17:58,202
[groaning]

280
00:18:02,873 --> 00:18:04,834
Mr. Tetsu is saying he'll forgive you.

281
00:18:04,917 --> 00:18:06,836
-So, get your money out.
-[breathing heavily]

282
00:18:08,337 --> 00:18:10,798
[Takao grunting] Wait!

283
00:18:16,012 --> 00:18:18,055
[chuckles, inhales]

284
00:18:18,806 --> 00:18:21,684
-[coins jingling]
-[exclaims]

285
00:18:21,767 --> 00:18:23,436
That's it?

286
00:18:24,395 --> 00:18:26,147
How sad is that?

287
00:18:26,230 --> 00:18:29,734
[exclaims] Great arm. [chuckles]

288
00:18:29,817 --> 00:18:30,985
Let's go.

289
00:18:31,777 --> 00:18:33,738
Life must be fun for you two.

290
00:18:34,697 --> 00:18:35,865
[Tetsu] What was that?

291
00:18:38,200 --> 00:18:40,745
You obviously have no doubts
about your lives...

292
00:18:41,704 --> 00:18:44,332
[breath trembling] It must be nice.

293
00:18:44,874 --> 00:18:46,959
[♪ melancholy music playing]

294
00:18:47,043 --> 00:18:48,878
-Hey.
-Sure.

295
00:18:53,299 --> 00:18:54,717
[groaning]

296
00:18:58,679 --> 00:19:00,139
[yelps]

297
00:19:05,728 --> 00:19:08,564
-[Tetsu chuckles]
-[goon] Watch your mouth, kid.

298
00:19:15,237 --> 00:19:16,697
You see...

299
00:19:17,990 --> 00:19:20,076
I died that day.

300
00:19:21,035 --> 00:19:23,245
I lost everything.

301
00:19:25,539 --> 00:19:27,833
And yet, here I am.

302
00:19:28,876 --> 00:19:31,253
Alive and shamefully breathing.

303
00:19:33,756 --> 00:19:35,132
[breathing shakily]

304
00:19:35,216 --> 00:19:36,842
I'm practically a zombie.

305
00:19:37,343 --> 00:19:38,636
A zombie, you see...

306
00:19:38,719 --> 00:19:40,054
What's your deal?

307
00:19:40,137 --> 00:19:41,889
Mumbling creepy shit.

308
00:19:43,557 --> 00:19:44,642
[Takao grunts]

309
00:19:52,900 --> 00:19:54,860
[breathing heavily]

310
00:19:54,944 --> 00:19:56,028
Hey...

311
00:19:57,697 --> 00:19:59,532
tell me, would you?

312
00:20:01,450 --> 00:20:03,828
How should I live on?

313
00:20:04,870 --> 00:20:08,249
How can I be like you,
living so shamelessly?

314
00:20:09,291 --> 00:20:10,292
Tell me...

315
00:20:11,210 --> 00:20:13,045
shit bugs.

316
00:20:16,966 --> 00:20:18,634
[groaning]

317
00:20:20,302 --> 00:20:21,429
[coughing]

318
00:20:23,305 --> 00:20:25,057
[screaming]

319
00:20:25,141 --> 00:20:27,685
[Tetsu] That hurts, doesn't it?

320
00:20:32,690 --> 00:20:34,984
What's with your obnoxious talking?

321
00:20:36,068 --> 00:20:39,447
If you're gonna bother people,
go kill yourself already.

322
00:20:40,030 --> 00:20:41,115
You piece of shit.

323
00:20:43,033 --> 00:20:44,452
[Takao grunting]

324
00:20:46,912 --> 00:20:48,622
-[Tetsu] Let's go.
-[goon] Sure.

325
00:20:49,123 --> 00:20:50,458
[Tetsu] I'm kinda hungry.

326
00:20:50,541 --> 00:20:51,834
[goon] Yeah, I'm hungry, too.

327
00:20:51,917 --> 00:20:53,085
[Tetsu] Wanna get some <i>gyudon?</i>

328
00:20:53,169 --> 00:20:55,421
[goon] <i>Gyudon?</i> Great idea.

329
00:20:55,504 --> 00:20:57,173
[Tetsu] I want one with <i>shirataki</i> noodles.

330
00:20:57,256 --> 00:20:59,258
-[goon] We'll find one with lots of 'em.
-Yeah.

331
00:20:59,341 --> 00:21:01,177
[Takao breathing shakily]

332
00:21:04,138 --> 00:21:05,431
[Takao grunts]

333
00:21:12,438 --> 00:21:13,481
[groans]

334
00:21:21,280 --> 00:21:22,615
He's right.

335
00:21:24,700 --> 00:21:26,243
I suppose...

336
00:21:26,911 --> 00:21:29,079
I'd be better off dead.

337
00:21:43,677 --> 00:21:45,304
[sighs]

338
00:22:02,655 --> 00:22:05,699
WE BUY OLD BOOKS - MIYAMA BOOKSTORE

339
00:22:08,953 --> 00:22:10,412
Books...

340
00:22:11,580 --> 00:22:12,873
Like they'd do any good now.

341
00:22:26,053 --> 00:22:29,932
THE FLOWERS OF EVIL

342
00:22:30,015 --> 00:22:31,851
-[♪ rock music playing]
-[gasps]

343
00:22:40,359 --> 00:22:41,902
[gasps]

344
00:22:48,450 --> 00:22:50,786
TO BE CONTINUED

345
00:22:50,870 --> 00:22:52,955
[♪ closing theme music playing]

346
00:23:47,927 --> 00:23:48,969
ON THE NEXT EPISODE

347
00:23:49,053 --> 00:23:52,640
[narrator] <i>Kasuga sees a resemblance</i>
<i>between Tokiwa and a girl he once knew.</i>

348
00:23:52,723 --> 00:23:56,560
<i>But that small moment of joy</i>
<i>is brutally torn apart.</i>

349
00:23:56,644 --> 00:23:58,729
<i>Next, on episode nine,</i>

350
00:23:58,812 --> 00:24:01,774
<i>What is Tokiwa's secret</i>
<i>that only Kasuga knows?</i>

351
00:24:01,857 --> 00:24:02,858
Translated by Yuka Kristi
